The paper deals with the complexity classification of Boolean surjective VCSPs, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of algorithms for solving these problems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the mathematical structure of the newly discovered tractable class, which is related to downsets and upsets, and thus can be classified under information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the study of graphs and coding theory, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS).
